value.0: "Welcome back. How can I help you?" Gelani turns her moon-eyed face to you slowly. She seems preoccupied with some thought or memory, but smiles softly at you all the same.
"What are we doing back here? I have no patience for this, <FirstName>."
"What? Murder! Help me!"

"Greetings, friend, and welcome to the Mossy Tree. If you need anything you should speak to Mr. Mossy." This halfling sips a glass of wine pausing occasionally to stare mournfully into its ruby depths.
"Godspeed, good <man/woman>."
"What is wrong? Why do you need me? Where are we going?"

value.0: "I feel disquieted right now. Probably because of the election, not that I'm involved in politics anymore. Please, ask someone else your questions."
"My name is Gelani and I am part owner of this establishment, along with Mr. Mossy. I was also something more than that once, but those days are gone."
"Sorry, I don't mean to be melancholy, but with the election happening, I long for the days when I was more involved in politics."

value.0: "I am always happy to speak to a customer."
"It isn't so dry when exciting things like the election and the Masked Man's invasion are going on. Right now is the most critical moment for a politician, and I have to miss out on it."

"Not so long ago, I was the master of the merchants' guild, a position I really loved. Unfortunately my leadership was usurped by Thaddeus Squilt, a notorious villain with a black heart, but a cunning mind."
"Thaddeus spread rumors about me, and the rumors were backed by a certain noble who, even now, makes a bid for leadership of this dear keep."
"That is like saying a dragon is a little dangerous. It's a gross understatement if I've ever heard one."
"Ask anyone with moral character in town and they will tell you that Thaddeus Squilt is completely untrustworthy. The rumors he started destroyed me."
"He may be more cunning, but he is hardly smarter. He is a terrible, foolish leader. His rumors destroyed my reputation, but he shall destroy the keep."
"Because I had supported some necessary tax increases in the past, Thaddeus persuaded others that I was planning on supporting a doubling in taxes; which I would never do."
"Unfortunately, with Sir Becket's help, Thaddeus's lies were believed and he became the new guildmaster. Now the entire keep is paying for his poor leadership."
"You think so? We barely survived the Masked Man's attack on the keep... the Banner did not. Part of the blame for his death lies with Thaddeus."
"Ever since Thaddeus stole my position, he has moved to block any increase in taxes. The only reason I ever supported the tax increases was so the Banner could afford to train and arm new guards."
"Now the guards are ill-equipped, inexperienced and demoralized. I do not envy the next Lord or Lady of the Keep."

"Sir Becket is like some evil demon come to us in man-flesh to lead us to our dooms. Every move he makes seems to lead us closer to chaos, rather than to a stable government where trade can flourish."
"Enivid is young and ignorant of political necessities. If she becomes the Lady of the Keep, she will quickly become frustrated with the authority of the guilds."
"Are these the only choices we have? A monster of chaos or an authoritative purist?"

value.0: "Very well. What did you want to discuss?"
"Come with you? Where? Why?"
Gelani raises an eyebrow at you and shakes her head. "I don't know what to do. Some of the others are pretty unhappy with the current situation."
"I guess I can. What choice do I have? Fine, let's go now."
"Why should I take such a chance? I need neither the ridicule nor the pain of losing again."
"I know. That is why I sit here and drink. Now, if you will excuse me..."
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> "How dare you speak to me that way! I tried, I truly did, but the others voted me out. I will do no such thing ever again!"
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> "How dare you speak to me that way... no... wait... you are right. Here I sit complaining, but refusing to do anything to change it."
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> "No... I am doomed to failure. I had the chance once and I lost it."
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> "You really think so? I suppose it is possible; there have been quite a few merchants displeased with Thaddeus."
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> "I can't. I know you are right, but it would be a wasted effort."
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> "I know it is. I have just... no, you are right. It is the only chance I have, if I am to help everyone."
"Thank you for the confidence, <FirstName>. I will go and gather the merchants for another vote. Hopefully, by tomorrow, I will be back in power."
"Come and see me in the merchants' guild office, later."
"It is best to stay hidden in shadows, pretty halfling. Leaders find trouble; <FirstName> needs to learn this lesson!"
"People react to threats in different ways. Perhaps with the threat of invasion, the other merchants might listen to another voice?"
"Thaddeus sounds like the kind of person who would do anything to gain power, no matter how despicable the deed. You need to stand against him, no matter how hard!"
"If this Thaddeus is as corrupt as you say he is, and I believe you speak the truth, do you not owe it to your guild to try to stop him?"
"You have given me much hope for the future, <FirstName>. You will have my vote in the election." Gelani offers you a formal bow, already seeming to consider you her Lord.
"The future looks bright, <Lord/Lady> <FirstName>. Best of luck."
"You need to take back your guild!"
<StartAction>[Attack]</Start>
